If the dead could see happenings on earth, then late Oba Lateef Akanni of Ado-Odo, Ogun State would be content with the kind of burial he has received. The first-class monarch joined his ancestors on Friday, January 7, and was buried according to Islamic rights. However, his burial rites would not be complete without the mandatory 41-day prayer. Between Ituah Ighodalo And Asiwaju Bola Tinubu Like Sayyu Dantata, Like Wale Tinubu Slated for today, and holding at Alamuwa Grammar School, Ado Odo, Ogun State, the event will be graced by top dignitaries from far and near including the Governor of Ogun State, Prince Dapo Abiodun, his deputy, Noimot Salako-Oloyede, and the Ooni of Ife, Oba Enitan Ogunwusi. Also expected at the colourful event are the paramount rulers in Ogun State including the Olu of Ilaro, Oba Kehinde Olugbenle, who will play host to other royal fathers from Ogun State at the event. A high point of the event will be the official launch of the Oba Abdul Lateef Adeniran Akanni Foundation, aimed at preserving the ideals for which the highly revered late monarch lived.